{"pageContext":{"id":"605211","parent":"__SOURCE__","slug":"china-ethics-committee-online-games-means","internal":{"contentDigest":"64abe838a6bbd0d83cc0ef754c192c0f","type":"ContentCoPost","owner":"default-site-plugin"},"children":[],"title":"China has an “ethics committee for online games” but nobody knows what that means","preview":{"source":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2.jpg","attachment_meta":{"width":707,"height":398,"sizes":{"thumbnail":{"width":100,"height":100,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-100x100.jpg"},"medium":{"width":350,"height":197,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-350x197.jpg"},"tia_thumb350_150":{"width":350,"height":150,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-350x150.jpg"},"tia_thumb60_60":{"width":60,"height":60,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-60x60.jpg"},"tia_thumb285_285":{"width":285,"height":285,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-285x285.jpg"},"tia_thumb727_300":{"width":707,"height":300,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-707x300.jpg"},"tia_thumb174_74":{"width":174,"height":74,"url":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2-174x74.jpg"}}}},"createdAt":"2018-12-10T06:00:31","content":"<p class=\"article-body-text arrow-placement\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\">China has formed a dedicated <a href=\"https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_2716062?from=singlemessage&amp;isappinstalled=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ethics Committee for Online Gaming</a>. State media says it’s denied licenses to nine games and advised 11 others to make changes to reduce “ethical risks.”</p>\n<p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\">What games? What risks? What does the ethics committee do? Nobody knows.</p>\n<p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\"><a href=\"http://m.weibo.cn/status/4314600482251215?\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">One Weibo user wrote</a>, “What does this mean? You have to review our ethics? I dare ask, are saints doing the reviews?”</p>\n<div class=\"related-person-group exclude\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\">\n<div class=\"related-person-group-wrapper hidden-sm-down gtm-onElementVisiblity\" data-v-212a770b=\"\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\" data-ev-category=\"Whatis button\" data-ev-action=\"Whatis widget impression\" data-ev-label=\"/who-what/how-weibo-became-chinas-most-popular-blogging-platform/article/2161847\" data-gtm-vis-first-on-screen-7381696_24=\"133414\">\n<div class=\"related-person-wrapper hidden-sm-down\" data-v-212a770b=\"\">\n<div class=\"related-person-widget up hide\" data-v-212a770b=\"\">\n<div class=\"related-person up\" data-v-212a770b=\"\">\n<div class=\"related-person-detail up\" data-v-212a770b=\"\">\n<div class=\"related-person-brief\" data-v-212a770b=\"\">\n<p>Weibo is a Twitter-like microblogging service used by hundreds of millions of users. Launched by Sina in 2009, it regularly censors topics deemed sensitive or inappropriate by the Chinese government.</p>\n<p>China is, of course, no stranger to regulation. And China’s gaming industry, the biggest in the world, is <a href=\"https://www.abacusnews.com/digital-life/how-apple-allowing-gamers-china-play-grand-theft-auto/article/2164301\" data-link-type=\"node\" data-link-subtype=\"article\" data-link-id=\"2164301\" data-link-href=\"/digital-life/how-apple-allowing-gamers-china-play-grand-theft-auto/article/2164301\" data-link-title=\"How Apple is allowing gamers in China to play Grand Theft Auto\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">full of red tape</a> right now. The government has virtually <a href=\"https://www.techinasia.com/china-games-industry-struggles-amid-shakeup\" data-link-type=\"node\" data-link-subtype=\"article\" data-link-id=\"2164301\" data-link-href=\"/digital-life/how-apple-allowing-gamers-china-play-grand-theft-auto/article/2164301\" data-link-title=\"How Apple is allowing gamers in China to play Grand Theft Auto\">put the gaming industry on hold</a> right now by not approving any new games since March – all thanks to a bureaucratic fight between two departments.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\">In fairness, China’s gaming space has been a bit like a virtual Wild West. There are tons of titles that push boundaries in various ways, whether in taste or by being <a href=\"https://www.abacusnews.com/playerunknowns-battlegrounds-clones-flood-chinese-smartphones/article/2131753\" data-link-type=\"node\" data-link-subtype=\"article\" data-link-id=\"2131753\" data-link-href=\"/playerunknowns-battlegrounds-clones-flood-chinese-smartphones/article/2131753\" data-link-title=\"PlayerUnknown's Battlegrounds clones flood Chinese smartphones\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">shameless clones</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\">Take <em><a href=\"http://This%20hit%20anime%20schoolgirl%20game%20looks%20Japanese,%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20from%20China/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Honkai Impact 3rd</a></em>, for instance. It’s an action game, but it stars anime schoolgirls. And one of the modes in the game allowed players to <a href=\"http://This%20hit%20anime%20schoolgirl%20game%20looks%20Japanese,%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20from%20China/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">poke at their bodies</a>, “touching” them in, well, you know the rest. After public criticism, it was removed from the game.</p>\n<figure class=\"img-caption-processed\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\"><div class=\"image\">\n<div class=\"wp-caption alignnone\">\n<img class=\"image-1320w caption\" title=\"Female characters could get mad depending on where players touched them -- or perhaps to put it more accurately, when players harassed them. (Picture: miHoYo)\" src=\"https://cdn1.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/styles/1320w/public/2018/12/07/maxresdefault_12.jpg?itok=edqBFtAG\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" data-src=\"https://cdn1.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/styles/1320w/public/2018/12/07/maxresdefault_12.jpg?itok=edqBFtAG\" data-style-type=\"default\" data-writer=\"Staff\"><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Female characters could get mad depending on where players touched them – or perhaps to put it more accurately, when players harassed them. / Image credit: miHoYo</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</figure><p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\">Still, since few know what the new ethics committee actually does, others on social media are turning to humor to explain it.</p>\n<p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\"><a href=\"https://m.weibo.cn/status/4314600482251215?\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">A Weibo user</a> referenced George Orwell’s 1984, “Is this the Ministry of Truth?”</p>\n<p class=\"article-body-text\" data-v-46c6605a=\"\"><a href=\"https://m.weibo.cn/status/4314600482251215?\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Another Weibo user</a> also sarcastically wrote, “This is a move to punish you plebs. You could have dedicated yourself to learning the socialist values. But instead, you choose to play games.”</p>\n<div>\n<p><em>For <span class=\"il\">more</span> on China tech, visit <a href=\"https://www.abacusnews.com/?utm_source=TIA&amp;utm_medium=partner&amp;utm_campaign=contentexchangeabacus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.abacusnews.com/?utm_source%3DTIA%26utm_medium%3Dpartner%26utm_campaign%3Dcontentexchangeabacus&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1544070450615000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGbIWMSvlKsQ5PgS4VKXGhL6TYC_A\">abacusnews.com</a> or subscribe to the newsletter via <a href=\"https://www.abacusnews.com/?utm_source=TIA&amp;utm_medium=partner&amp;utm_campaign=contentexchangeabacus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.abacusnews.com/?utm_source%3DTIA%26utm_medium%3Dpartner%26utm_campaign%3Dcontentexchangeabacus&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1544070450615000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGbIWMSvlKsQ5PgS4VKXGhL6TYC_A\">abacusnews.com/newsletter</a> for the latest China tech news, reviews and product launches.</em></p>\n</div>\n<div><em>Copyright (c) 2018. South China Morning Post Publishers Ltd. All rights reserved.</em></div>","categories":[{"id":"39658","name":"News","slug":"news"}],"author":{"name":"Josh Ye","image":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/authors/241023.jpg?v=1544417017"},"seo":{"title":"China has an “ethics committee for online games” but nobody knows what that means","description":"Nine games have allegedly been banned, but we don’t know which ones.","image":"https://cdn.techinasia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Xiaomi-Bluetooth-game-controller-2.jpg"}}}